{"parse":{"title":"Raw Rockscale Cod","pageid":63421,"wikitext":{"*":"<noinclude>__NOTOC__</noinclude>{{{{{tpl|tooltip}}}\n|mode={{{mode|}}}\n|arg={{{arg|}}}\n|icon=INV_Misc_Fish_04\n|name=Raw Rockscale Cod\n|quality=common\n|level=25\n|stack=20\n|effect=<u>Use</u>: Restores 552 health over 24 sec. Must remain seated while eating.\n|sell={{Cost|c=4}} each\n|ilvl=35\n}}<noinclude>\nA '''Raw Rockscale Cod''' can be eaten without cooking, but it is much better when cooked.\n{{clrl}}\n==Source==\nThis fish can be caught by [[fishing]] in the waters of mid level zones such as [[Feralas]] and [[Stranglethorn Vale]].\n\nThis fish will also drop occasionally from various level 34-39 creatures including various Murlocs and Turtles as well as others.\n\n==Raw Rockscale Cod as an Ingredient==\n\n===Cooking===\n*[[Rockscale Cod]]\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{elinks-item|6362}}\n{{Elink|link=http://www.elsanglin.com/fish/raw_rockscale_cod.html |site=El's Extreme Anglin' |icon=elsanglin}}\n\n[[Category:World of Warcraft common fished items]]\n[[Category:World of Warcraft food items]]\n[[Category:World of Warcraft cooking ingredient items]]\n\n</noinclude>"}}}